Welcome To The Genealogy Beyong One Generation Tutorial
Match the tree terms with its definition
What are the three major things learned in the previous slides?
Family is a group of one or more parents and their children living together as a unit in a household.
To navigate through the training, press the play, previous, and next buttons from the beginning to end.
In this training, how many parts were on the labeled tree?

Click On Either Side To Locate The Hot Spot For For Your Family Tree. When you find it, you will then transition to the next slide to learn about the various places and online sources that will have resources to help you independently compile your family tree beyond one generation.
Fill In The Blank Dad and Mom

Abraham Lincoln was born on February 12, 1809 in Larue County, Kentucky and died in the Peterson House on April 15, 1865. His parents were Thomas Lincoln and Nancy Hanks. In this story, how many generations are being represented?
Fill In The Blank Harriet Tubman

George Washington was the first president of the United States from 1789 to 1797. He was born February 22, 1732, Westmoreland County, VA. He died December 14, 1799, George Washington's Mount Vernon, Mount Vernon, VA. He married Martha Washington in 1759. George Washington parents were Augustine Washington and Mary Ball. His paternal grandparents were Lawrence Washington and Mildred Warner. His maternal grandparents were Joseph Ball and Mary Montague. In this story, how many generations are represented?
